SECTION 2 — THE CORE PROBLEM
==================================================

Title:
“Why supplier sustainability transition is difficult today”

4 premium problem cards.

CARD 1:
Fragmented Supplier Data

Supplier sustainability information exists across invoices, utility bills, spreadsheets, procurement systems, and PDFs with no unified visibility.

CARD 2:
Limited Supplier Transition Visibility

Enterprises struggle to identify which suppliers require sustainability engagement or operational improvement.

CARD 3:
Manual ESG Assessment Processes

Supplier sustainability analysis is time-consuming, inconsistent, and difficult to scale across large supply chains.

CARD 4:
Disconnected Transition Ecosystem

Vendors, consultants, certifications, subsidies, and financing opportunities are fragmented and difficult to coordinate.

